The paper deals with a technique to improve the effectiveness of batch normalization in deep learning models, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically applies the technique to object detection and image classification, which falls under the computer vision subfield of CS. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques and neural networks, which are relevant to cs.LG and cs.NE. The proposed compensation technique based on Taylor polynomials involves mathematical concepts, which could be relevant to cs.AI. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, which could be relevant to cs.CL.
